dotfiles
========

Bootstrapping
-------------

In the `scripts/` module stow itself is included. You can call it from the
repository root to install the script and any other module you want like this:

	./scripts/dot-local/bin/stow -S scripts

Claude Code
-----------

Setting MCP servers is not supported via the settings JSON file I have checked
in and the `.claude.json` is not something you should not check in. The two MCP
servers I regularly use are Chrome DevTools and Perplexity:

	claude mcp add chrome-devtools --scope user -- npx -y chrome-devtools-mcp@latest
	claude mcp add perplexity      --scope user -- npx -y @perplexity-ai/mcp-server@latest

Setting up the environment variables to configure proxy endpoints and tokens is
something which is not covered for obvious reasons.
